description:
BBC
Top Gear - Best of the Stig

Some say he invented Betamax, and its subsequent failure is the reason why he never talks. All we know is that this DVD is a tribute to the most epic Stig moments of all time.

&gt;&gt; What's the quickest way to get across London? Jeremy, James and Richard choose a car, a bike and a powerboat, while a disorientated Stig tackles public transport. Is it possible to get a tube and a bus sideways?

&gt;&gt; Using an old BMW, a tank of home-grown diesel and enough caffeine to put their eyes on stalks, the boys enter a 24-hour race. Problem is, they're rubbish at it. Luckily, the rules allow for a fourth driver...

&gt;&gt; And then there are the greatest power laps we could find. Stig in his element, right on the limit, blitzing an Apollo to a record, drifting the Caterham R500. Taming a Koenigsegggggggg with a rear wing and...

...crashing right off the track in a Koenigsegggggggg
without a rear wing, The Stig's only recorded prang!
